hpnicfFtmManMIB.name: hpnicfFtmManMIB
hpnicfFtmManMIB.description: this MIB will maintain Fabric topology management. The MIB includes unit-id, unit-name and fabric authentication information.

hpnicfFtmUnitTable.name: hpnicfFtmUnitTable
hpnicfFtmUnitTable.description: A table of informations of XRN-Fabric Unit.

hpnicfFtmUnitEntry.name: hpnicfFtmUnitEntry
hpnicfFtmUnitEntry.description: An entry for configuring unit informations of XRN-Fabric.

hpnicfFtmIndex.name: hpnicfFtmIndex
hpnicfFtmIndex.description: The unique index of a unit.

hpnicfFtmUnitID.name: hpnicfFtmUnitID
hpnicfFtmUnitID.description: Identifer of unit in fabric. Its value should be between 1 and the maximum which defines in product specification. An exception is described in description of hpnicfFtmNumberMode. In that case, the value of this object remains its original value after set to zero.

hpnicfFtmUnitName.name: hpnicfFtmUnitName
hpnicfFtmUnitName.description: Name of unit in XRN-Fabric. It consists of no more than 64 characters.

hpnicfFtmUnitRole.name: hpnicfFtmUnitRole
hpnicfFtmUnitRole.description: Role of unit in XRN-Fabric. One unit in a XRN-Fabric acts as master role and others act as slave roles

hpnicfFtmNumberMode.name: hpnicfFtmNumberMode
hpnicfFtmNumberMode.description: Numbering Mode of unit in XRN-Fabric. If the unit ID is assigned by the auto numbering algorithm, the numbering mode will be automatic numbering; if the unit ID (hpnicfFtmUnitID) is assigned by the user, the numbering mode will be manual numbering; if hpnicfFtmUnitID is set to be zero, the numbering mode will become automatic numbering.

hpnicfFtmAuthValue.name: hpnicfFtmAuthValue
hpnicfFtmAuthValue.description: Authentication value of XRN-Fabric Feature. ftm_none mode means no authentication. In simple mode, the value is password of a string of 1 to 16 charactors. While in md5 mode, the value is key of a string within 16 charactors.

hpnicfFtmFabricVlanID.name: hpnicfFtmFabricVlanID
hpnicfFtmFabricVlanID.description: The object is used for get and set the Fabric VlanID. Only is the equipment not in the stacking status, the value can be set.

hpnicfFtmFabricType.name: hpnicfFtmFabricType
hpnicfFtmFabricType.description: Topology type of Fabric. outofStack means this unit is not in stack.

hpnicfFtmUnitIDChange.name: hpnicfFtmUnitIDChange
hpnicfFtmUnitIDChange.description: When unit id changes in fabric, this trap is sent with unit index and its new id .

hpnicfFtmUnitNameChange.name: hpnicfFtmUnitNameChange
hpnicfFtmUnitNameChange.description: When unit name changes in fabric, this trap is sent with unit index and its new name.

hpnicfFtmMIBCompliance.name: hpnicfFtmMIBCompliance
hpnicfFtmMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for FTM implementing the MIB.

hpnicfFtmConfigGroup.name: hpnicfFtmConfigGroup
hpnicfFtmConfigGroup.description: The basic collection of objects for sending trap of FTM Management.

hpnicfFtmNotificationGroup.name: hpnicfFtmNotificationGroup
hpnicfFtmNotificationGroup.description: The basic collection of objects for sending trap of FTM Management.
